Raspberry pi v3 or higher used
2016-05-27 raspbian-jessie operating system used

To install Python on Ubuntu, run

sudo apt-get install python python-tk
Or for Python 3

sudo apt-get install python python3-tk


sudo apt-get install python3-matplotlib
	- for live graph of the reading of the sensors 

sudo apt-get install python-pip
sudo pip install numpy
sudo pip install pandas

>> TkTreectrl

    python setup.py install

sudo apt-get install tcl-dev tk-dev mesa-common-dev libjpeg-dev libtogl-dev


    # ./configure --with-tcl=/usr/lib/tcl8.4 --with-tk=/usr/lib/tk8.4
    # make
    # make install

offline text to speech
pip3 install pyttsx3
google text to speech
pip3 install gTTS


to run the program

sudo python3 MainApplication.py